            {% endif %}</div><div data-section-id="pf-fc3d" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jlRLRk bizPpK pf-8_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-lkgTHX eDNqWj"><div class="sc-fFeiMQ etkQEf pf-9_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-FNXRL gpaAAN pf-10_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-11_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-13_">Employee burnout: The hidden epidemic in health and social care sector</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098773" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098773 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_1000x.png?v=1685098773 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685098773 320w" width="1669" height="1113" alt="Employee Burnout: The Hidden Epidemic in Health and Social Care Sector - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Employee Burnout: The Hidden Epidemic in Health and Social Care Sector - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-14_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-3016" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jlRLRk bizPpK pf-15_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-lkgTHX eDNqWj"><div class="sc-fFeiMQ etkQEf pf-16_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-FNXRL gpaAAN pf-17_"><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-18_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-20_">Employee burnout, defined by the World Health Organisation as "<i>a syndrome conceptualised as resulting from chronic workplace stress that has not been successfully managed</i>", is a crisis afflicting health and social care services across the globe. Characterised by feelings of exhaustion, cynicism, and reduced professional efficacy, burnout affects both leaders and employees, becoming a significant driver of the talent shortage and presenting a costly challenge for the sector.<br>
<br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> discusses this topical issue and provides practical tips for health and social care managers to deal with workplace burnout.
<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-21_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-23_">Prevalence of workplace burnout
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prevalence_of_workplace_burnout_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098885" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prevalence_of_workplace_burnout_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098885 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prevalence_of_workplace_burnout_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685098885 320w" width="1766" height="1179" alt="Prevalence of workplace burnout - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Prevalence of workplace burnout - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-24_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-27_">In 2022, an estimated 100 million employees worldwide left their jobs, a large proportion due to burnout. In the United States alone, 50.5 million employees quit their jobs.
<br><br>The UK's health and social care sector has been under immense pressure due to the COVID-19 pandemic and the inherent stresses associated with care roles.
<br><br>According to Mental Health UK, 46% of UK workers feel 'more prone to extreme levels of stress' compared with a year ago (March 2020), while only 15% feel 'less prone to extreme levels of stress'. Burnout is often misunderstood and stigmatised despite its prevalence, impacting employees' health and well-being and employers' productivity.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-28_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-30_">Understanding burnout and establishing a culture of empathy

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_burnout_and_establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098984" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_burnout_and_establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685098984 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_burnout_and_establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685098984 320w" width="1382" height="922" alt="Understanding burnout and establishing a culture of empathy - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Understanding burnout and establishing a culture of empathy - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-31_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-34_">No√©mie Le Pertel's recent article in Harvard Business Review brings to light the challenge managers face when an employee opens up about burnout. She emphasises that the initial reaction should not be to dismiss or downplay concerns. Instead, it is crucial to treat burnout with seriousness and empathy.
<br><br>Le Pertel proposes these three pivotal questions to discern between temporary stress and burnout:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-htJRVC nISvC pf-35_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-cbTzjv NvZVs pf-36_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-38_">Do they feel competent?
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-cbTzjv NvZVs pf-39_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-41_">Do they feel emotionally exhausted?
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-cbTzjv NvZVs pf-42_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-44_">Do they experience physical symptoms?
</span></li></ul><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-45_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-47_">These questions help provide insight into the employee's self-perception, emotional state, and work-related attitudes.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-48_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-50_">Identifying root causes and implementing solutions

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_root_causes_and_implementing_solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099076" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_root_causes_and_implementing_solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099076 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_root_causes_and_implementing_solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685099076 320w" width="1475" height="829" alt="Identifying root causes and implementing solutions - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Identifying root causes and implementing solutions - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-51_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-52_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-54_">Once a leader understands the employee's experience of burnout, the following steps involve identifying the root causes and implementing immediate and long-term solutions. These causes can originate from within the workplace, such as an imbalance between work demands and available resources, or outside work, like financial stress or caregiving responsibilities.
<br><br>Immediate measures include delegating some of their workloads, renegotiating deadlines, or offering time off. Long-term strategies involve adjusting job responsibilities, providing flexibility in how and where they work, or investing in their personal and professional development.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-55_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-57_">Sustaining change over time

</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sustaining_change_over_time_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099294" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sustaining_change_over_time_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099294 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sustaining_change_over_time_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685099294 320w" width="1486" height="991" alt="Sustaining change over time - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Sustaining change over time - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-58_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-59_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-61_">Addressing burnout is an ongoing process. Regular check-ins with the employee can help monitor progress, adjust strategies as required, and reaffirm your commitment to their well-being. By implementing these steps, leaders can establish an empathetic, supportive environment that effectively tackles burnout and fosters retention.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-62_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-64_">Benefits of addressing burnout
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Benefits_of_addressing_burnout_-_What_is_corporate_strategy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099417" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Benefits_of_addressing_burnout_-_What_is_corporate_strategy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099417 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Benefits_of_addressing_burnout_-_What_is_corporate_strategy_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685099417 320w" width="1905" height="1270" alt="Benefits of addressing burnout - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Benefits of addressing burnout - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-65_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-66_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-68_">Addressing burnout can result in numerous benefits, from improved employee well-being and reduced turnover to increased productivity and job satisfaction. The quality of care provided can also improve, a crucial factor for patient outcomes within the health and social care sector.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-69_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-71_">Conclusion and recommendations
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Conclusion_and_recommendations_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099552" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Conclusion_and_recommendations_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1685099552 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_Burnout_The_Hidden_Epidemic_in_Health_and_Social_Care_Sector_-_Conclusion_and_recommendations_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.png?v=1685099552 320w" width="1866" height="1228" alt="Employee Burnout: The Hidden Epidemic in Health and Social Care Sector - Conclusion and recommendations - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Employee Burnout: The Hidden Epidemic in Health and Social Care Sector - Conclusion and recommendations - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-uojGG kTBJzQ pf-72_"/><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-73_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-75_">Employee burnout is a hidden epidemic that can no longer be ignored, especially in the health and social care sector. Addressing this crisis requires empathy, understanding, proactive dialogue, and continuous engagement. It's not just about treating symptoms, but about implementing systemic changes to tackle the root causes of burnout.<br><br>Health and social care leaders are encouraged to create an open dialogue about mental health and burnout, invest in regular training for managers, and implement systemic changes to promote a more empathetic and supportive work culture. Remember, a healthy team is a productive team. <br><br>Let's work together to build a resilient, empathetic, and burnout-free health and social care sector.
